                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>A consular conference of officers from the Union of South Africa and Rhodesia was
                    held at Pretoria and Johannesburg on May 26, 27, and 28, 1953. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RGH1">G. Hayden Raynor</persName>, Director of the Office of
                    British Commonwealth and Northern European Affairs, was present for the
                    conference, which was largely given over to a review of current problems of
                    mutual interest, particularly in the light of expected reductions in staff and
                    operating expenses. A two-page summary report on the conference was transmitted
                    to the Department as an enclosure to despatch 470, June 9, 1953, from
                    Johannesburg. (120.4345A/6–953)</p>
                <p>For an account of the previous consular conference in Africa, see telegram 32,
                    March 14, 1952, from Capetown, <ref target="#pg_4">page 4</ref>. No other
                    consular or diplomatic conference of American officers serving in Africa appears
                    to have taken place in Africa during the 1952–1954 period.</p>
            </div>
